// RUN: not --crash triton-opt %s --nvgpu-warp-specialization="capability=100 num-stages=1 smem-budget=524288" 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// Characterization of the HSTU reduce_dq "compute fold" TMEM reuse-order
// blocker (bug #12 class in .llms/rules/partition-scheduler-bugs.md).
//
// Real pre-warp-specialization IR (post PartitionSchedulingMeta) for
// _hstu_attn_bwd_redq compiled with the experimental compute fold
// (HSTU_COMPUTE_FOLD=1): dk = tl.dot(act_qk_trans, do, dk) [dv, loc 3374] and
// dk = tl.dot(dqk_trans, q, dk) [dk_attn, loc 3402] both accumulate into the
// loop-carried dk slot. The fold does NOT collapse them into one TMEM tile: it
// lowers to two distinct tmem_allocs joined by a partition-4 tmem_load ->
// partition-0 tmem_store bridge, and both are annotated onto one dk buffer.id.
// The memory planner assigns them the same buffer.id (14 for the group-0 dk
// slot), so doCodePartition builds a single-copy TMEM reuse group of 7 channels
// (4 dv @loc3374 + 3 dk_attn @loc3402), all at buffer.offset 0 (temporal reuse,
// not spatial packing). Because the two accumulating writers are program-ordered
// only through the cross-partition bridge, orderReuseGroupChain finds no unique
// total write/read order, so WSCodePartition (~L3406) fails loudly rather than
// emit an unsound reuse barrier.
//
// smem-budget is raised so allocation clears the SMEM check and reaches the
// TMEM reuse-order check (the shipped budget trips an earlier SMEM-overflow
// error first).
//
// NOTE: the compute fold no longer PRODUCES this two-tile IR --
// ChainAccumulatorInPlace (in tritongpu-optimize-accumulator-init) now coalesces
// the two chained dk dots into one in-place TMEM accumulation, so no such reuse
// group forms end-to-end. This module is a FROZEN pre-fix capture kept as a
// defensive guard that WSCodePartition still fails loudly (rather than emitting
// an unsound reuse barrier) if any future kernel presents an unorderable >=3
// buffer single-copy TMEM reuse group. See accumulator-init-chain-fuse.mlir for
// the positive test of the coalescing that prevents this shape.

// CHECK: LLVM ERROR: TMEM reuse group with >= 3 buffers has no unique dependency-chain order
// CHECK-SAME: buffer.id=14 members=7

